Acu.description: "Acu" (ah-kyoo) is a 2.1 solo Extreme Demon created, published, and verified by neigefeu on April 22, 2020. It is considered one of the first modern-style Extreme Demon levels to ever be released. A wide majority of players consider this to be a low-end Extreme Demon and a good entry-level Extreme Demon due to how accessible it is. The level is often considered by the community to be fun and consistent, but some disagree.

Nine Circles.description: "Nine Circles" (commonly abbreviated to NC) is a 1.9 solo Hard Demon level created, verified and published by Zobros. Nine Circles is the second most downloaded and liked level not featured in a map pack or gauntlet and one of the most iconic levels in Geometry Dash, receiving acclaim for its gameplay, design, effects and difficulty. Nine Circles and its design inspired many other users to create levels using similar visual effects, gameplay, and structuring, referred to as Nine Circles levels.

Bloodbath.description: "Bloodbath" is a 1.9 Extreme Demon mega-collaboration level hosted, verified and published by Riot on 12 August 2015. Following its verification, it was placed at #1 on the Demonlist. Barely any other level would challenge this position for over a year until Sakupen Hell by TrusTa was released, marking the beginning of Bloodbath's descent in perceived difficulty. It is the second instalment of the community-designated "Apocalyptic Trilogy" of similarly-themed Extreme Demon levels, succeeding Cataclysm and preceding Aftermath. A buffed and extended remake, Bloodlust, was verified by knobbelboy and released in 2.0. The first victor of the level was Quasar on 13 March 2016, 7 months after the verification. The level that almost dethroned Bloodbath was "WcropoliX" verified by BlassCFB on 30 July 2016, but it was rated only 8 years after its verification.

Change of Scene.description: "Change of Scene" is a 2.1 solo Easy Demon created, verified and published by bli. bli created this level for the Discord Gauntlet Contest, hosted by Viprin, with the Top 10 best levels planned to be included in two official gauntlets with five levels, each requiring all entries to have two distinct modes, a normal mode and an alternate mode toggleable at the first five seconds of the level. The level was released on 2 May 2023, around fifteen minutes before the contest deadline. The level shifts through several themes: theatre, films, video games and simulation. An alternate mode can be toggled on at the beginning of the level, adding bosses to many sections and altering the designs and effects. The first mode intends to feel like pure fiction, with the second mode bringing everything to life with more realistic designs.

Demon Park.description: "Demon Park" is a 1.1 solo Easy Demon level created, verified and published by M2coL (formerly MidM2coL) on 17 October 2013. This level is the first ever Demon level, inspiring the addition of the Demon rating in Update 1.3 and is now considered one of the easiest. It is the first level in Demon Pack 1.

Creo.description: Creo is an electronic music artist. His real name is Clemens Michael Höberth and he lives in Vienna, Austria. He has been making music for over 14 years. His music is used often in the popular game Geometry Dash in making custom levels, with his most popular song being Dimension, due to the popularity of the level Black Blizzard by KrmaL.

Waterflame.description: Waterflame is the stage name of Christian Mejlænder Krogsvold, a self-taught Norwegian video game composer, sound designer, and pixel artist born on February 26, 1989, in Oslo. He began composing music as a teenager in 2002, originally uploading tracks to Newgrounds under the alias Chainsaw_09.

Zoink.description: Zoink (formerly Z01nk, zZoink in-game) is a skilled American player in Geometry Dash. He is widely considered to be one of the best players in the game, having beaten numerous top Extreme Demons with incredibly low attempt counts. He is the second player ever to complete the entire Top 75 hardest Demons on the Demonlist, following in the footsteps of nSwish.

Michigun.description: Michigun (9 December 1996 - March 2021) was an Austrian mobile player in Geometry Dash. Known for his use of triple-spikes in his levels, which became his trademark, Michigun was also recognized as one of the fastest star-grinders in the game. He amassed a total of 61,639 stars, 12,502 user coins, 16,661 diamonds, 1,000 Demons and 17 creator points. Michigun also created numerous levels inspired by temples from The Legend of Zelda series.

CherryTeam.description: Cherry Team (*cherryteam* in-game, also known as CherryBT, [cherry] and Cherry) is a creating team with many experienced layout creators, decorators and GFX artists. They are best known for their Extreme Demon projects, such as Void Wave, Cannon Bay, cytokinesis, Mayhem and the Top 10 levels KOCMOC and Firework, the latter of which briefly became the hardest Demon in the game. The team was founded and led by Vernam.

Cataclysm.description: "Cataclysm" is a 1.9/2.0 Extreme Demon level created, hack-verified and published by Ggb0y on 2 January 2015. The level was later updated and verified in 2.0 by Riot on 15 January 2016, who uploaded the new version to his account, where it is currently rated. Upon its release, it was featured and instantly became the hardest Demon level in Geometry Dash, historically tied with "ICE Carbon Diablo X". The level received acclaim for its difficulty and design and received accreditation for popularising the red and black "hell" theme in Extreme Demon levels. Cataclysm remains the second most-liked Extreme Demon in the game and one of the most popular and influential levels of all time, with its creation widely considered a turning point in the game's history. It is the first instalment of the community's classic "Apocalyptic Trilogy" of similarly-themed Extreme Demon levels, preceding "Bloodbath" and "Aftermath".

LIMBO.description: "LIMBO" is a 2.1 Extreme Demon mega-collaboration level hosted and published by MindCap, co-hosted by Djoxy and verified by BGram on 26 November 2022 after 109,490 attempts. The level is designed in a 1.9 style with an indigo, dark blue and red colour palette. MindCap intended the level to be the hardest memory Demon without relying on visual interference while implementing unique gameplay mechanics.

Slaughterhouse.description: "Slaughterhouse" is a 2.1 Extreme Demon mega-collaboration level hosted by IcEDCave and verified by Doggie, initially hack-verified by SpaceUK. It is loosely based on IcEDCave's old impossible level of the same name, created out of IcEDCave's dissatisfaction with the original level being his sole legacy in the community. The level was initially released as an impossible level in April 2021 but was later nerfed to place in the Top 5 on the Demonlist. However, multiple verifiers failed to beat it, leading to a revised version to compete for the top spot on the Demonlist, sparking a two-week verification race. SpaceUK claimed to have verified it on 24 October 2021 but was later discovered to have hacked it. The verifier title was rightfully passed to its first victor, Doggie, who legitimately completed the level on 19 December 2021. "Slaughterhouse" held the #1 spot on the Demonlist for a large part of 2022, establishing itself as one of the game's most iconic and influential top levels. Its impact has been notable since its release, inspiring other levels like "KOCMOC" and "The Rock House". While some players criticize its gameplay, particularly finding it tedious at the pre-drop, it is widely praised for its immersive atmosphere, enhanced by its music and design. IcEDCave later hosted a prequel called GRIEF, a direct remake of his 2015 "Slaughterhouse", set to be verified by Doggie.

VSC.description: "VSC" (short for Veri SuBBo Challenge) is a wave and spam challenge created by Bo and decorated by Woomy. It was verified by Yossarian on 21 September 2021 with a fluke from 48%. This level has been ranked #1 on the Challenge List for over 3 years, or 1312 days, before being moved to #2 by" Illusion of Hell" on 25 April 2025, verified by OverGD.

Ultra Violence.description: "Ultra Violence" is a 2.1 solo Medium Demon level created and published by Xender Game and verified by Viprin. The level has been praised for its decoration and animated boss fights and is considered by most to be one of Xender Game's best-looking levels.

Tartarus.description: "Tartarus" (formerly known as "Silent Akbar") is a 1.9-2.1 Extreme Demon mega-collaboration level created and hosted by Riot. The level was designed to be almost humanly impossible and thus was published by Riot to challenge the player community. Three players made significant progress on the level: Mullsy, Dolphy and MetaManRB. It was ultimately verified and published by Dolphy on 6 January 2020 and ranked at #1 on the Demonlist, surpassing Zodiac. Tartarus became the first of a new trilogy of hell-themed Top 1 levels hosted by Riot and was succeeded by Acheron, verified by Zoink on 23 August 2022, and a humanly impossible level "Aeternus".

HOW.description: "HOW" is a 2.1 solo normal level created and published by Spu7Nix on 14 August 2020. This level utilizes highly innovative 3D effects and animations. It has a sequel called "WHAT".

Death Moon.description: "Death Moon" is a 1.9 solo Easy Demon level created, published and verified by Caustic, the emergency user account of FunnyGame. It is an art-based, hell-themed level centered on apocalyptic visuals. "Death Moon" is one of the most acclaimed levels in Geometry Dash and often appears on lists of the greatest levels ever made, receiving praise for its intricate art, music, gameplay and innovative effects, and is the eighth most-liked Demon in the game. It is the fifth and last level of the Cursed Gauntlet, after iSpyWithMyLittleEye.

WHAT.description: "WHAT" is a 2.1 hard level created and published by Spu7Nix and verified by AeonAir on 6 October 2024. The level is a sequel to HOW, featuring more elaborate 3D effects produced with external programming.

Bloodlust.description: "Bloodlust" is a 2.0/2.1 Extreme Demon mega-collaboration level hosted by Manix648 and verified and published by Knobbelboy on 20 February 2018 after being dropped by its previous verifier Quasar. It is a buffed and extended remake of Bloodbath. Upon release, the level was placed at #1 on the Demonlist, surpassing "Plasma Pulse Finale". "Bloodlust" generated significant discussion for its extension and jump in difficulty compared to its predecessor, still the hardest level upon the remake's announcement. It is known for its detailed effects and designs, stylistic hellish visuals and difficult gameplay.

Nexus.description: Nexus is a skilled American-Mexican player and moderator in Geometry Dash. Nexus' most difficult Demons include Bloodlust, The Yandere, Plasma Pulse Finale, Sonic Wave, Yatagarasu, Dole Damos, Freedom08, Digital Descent, Killbot, Omicron, Artificial Ascent, Black Blizzard, Hatred, BuTiTi III, Astral Divinity, and Glitched Memories. On his YouTube channel, Nexus showcases various levels, from Extreme Demons to unknown and unrated. He often publishes videos of unique and innovative levels, and many people credit his channel as where they found certain levels.

Geode Team.description: Geode is an open-source mod loader and development kit (SDK) for Geometry Dash, designed to simplify the installation, management, and creation of mods. Compatible with multiple platforms (Windows, macOS, Android, and experimental iOS support), it integrates directly into the game with a built-in mod browser. Developed by the Geode Team, an active group of contributors, Geode aims to unify and streamline the modding experience while improving compatibility between mods. The founding and core members include HJfod, altalk23, matcool, Camila314, and Cvolton.

F-777.description: Jesse Levi Valentine (born on March 28, 1993), better known by his stage name F-777, is a Canadian electronic music producer and YouTuber. He creates a diverse range of electronic music, from orchestral and techno to high-energy dubstep, and his tracks have been featured in several popular games, most notably Geometry Dash, where many of his songs are included in the official game soundtrack.

NightKilla.description: NIGHTkilla (often stylized as NightKilla) is the alias of American electronic music producer Stephen Crouse, who has also released music under the names Rukkus and Realistik. His breakout came with the track "Nine Circles", posted on Newgrounds in 2013 and later associated with a popular demon level created by Zobros, which significantly boosted its reach. Other standout tracks include Fairydust, Problematic, Sweet Dreams, and Classical, all staples in custom levels and frequently used by players, even though none made it into the official soundtrack

Dimrain47.description: Clayton Tremmel (born in 1988), better known by his alias Dimrain47, is an American electronic music composer and producer. He began releasing fast-paced techno and melodic electronica tracks on Newgrounds in 2005 when he was about 15 years old. His most iconic song, "At the Speed of Light", saw renewed popularity when featured in the famous Geometry Dash level Cataclysm by Ggb0y, as well as other extreme demon levels, solidifying his legacy within the game’s community . After a prolonged break, he briefly returned to music in 2019 and has since reinvented himself as an instructor of composition rather than a full-time producer. His early work remains influential in rhythm games like Geometry Dash and osu!

Viprin.description: Viprin, also known as Vip, Vooper, and Voop, is a Norwegian player and Elder Moderator renowned for hosting official community events, including The Geometry Dash Awards, Gauntlet Contests, and Icon Contests, alongside RobTop. With over 130 rated levels, Viprin ranks #3 on the Creators Leaderboard and is widely known for his contributions to mega-collaborations such as Artificial Ascent, HyperSonic, Yatagarasu, and Ouroboros.

RobTop.description: Robert Nicholas Christian Topala (born on February 23, 1987), widely known by his pseudonym RobTop (also RubRub or Zhenmuron), is a Swedish game developer and founder of RobTop Games, the studio behind Geometry Dash. He initially studied civil engineering before pursuing game development, creating early Newgrounds and mobile games like Bounce Ball Thingy and Boomlings before releasing Geometry Dash on August 13, 2013 for iOS/Android and later for PC and Mac on December 22, 2014 RobTop was the sole designer, programmer, and composer of Geometry Dash, working with basic programming skills and drawing inspiration from titles like The Impossible Game, BIT.TRIP RUN!, and Super Meat Boy. He continues to oversee all aspects of the game and its sequels, including Geometry Dash Meltdown, World, and SubZero. Within the community, RobTop is both lauded for his creative vision and critiqued for handling of level ratings and moderation, a topic frequently discussed on platforms like Reddit. Nonetheless, he remains the central force behind the ongoing development, updates, and community engagement for the Geometry Dash franchise.

Sunix.description: Sunix (formerly Deam, ʟSunix in-game) is a skilled Mexican, known for swiftly beating difficult levels such as Sakupen Hell, Erebus, Digital Descent, Betrayal of Fate, Phobos, Athanatos, Quantum Processing, and Yatagarasu, as well as for being the verifier of Sonic Wave and Devil Vortex. He is also known for completing Bloodbath multiple times, as well as completing his own buffed version. His Top 5 currently include Bloodlust, Plasma Pulse Finale, Gamma, Deimos, and Sonic Wave. He was widely known as one of the best players in the game in 2017 due to his completion of the majority of the Top 100 Demons.

Riot.description: Riot is a renowned and experienced American. Widely considered one of the best players of all time, he is known for hosting and verifying the 1.9 Extreme Demon level Bloodbath, as well as hosting the 2.1 Extreme Demons Tartarus and Acheron, all of which had been the hardest Demon levels upon release, and establishing what would become the Demonlist. During his initial period in the game, Riot completed several of the former hardest levels. His most notable being ICE Carbon Diablo X, Cataclysm, Crimson Clutter, A Bizarre Phantasm, and Retention. Following his dropped attempt at verifying the 1.9 former hardest Demon Sonic Wave and various scattered Extreme Demon completions, Riot's activity in Geometry Dash dwindled before he officially quit the game on June 17, 2018. Riot would return to Geometry Dash in 2020 following an incident in which his YouTube channel was terminated, ending his over two-year-long absence with the upload of his completion of Sonic Wave, his current hardest completion, on October 31, 2020. About five months after this, he posted a video of him achieving 59% and a run of 56-97% on Zodiac. He would then complete Sakupen Hell, Aftermath, Phobos, Athanatos, and Auditory Breaker in the span of a few days. He is currently trying to go for Tidal Wave as his next hardest and last completion in Geometry Dash.

nSwish.description: nSwish was a skilled American Geometry Dash player. During the 2019-2020 era, he was considered by many to be the best player in the game, as he became the first player to have ever completed the entire Top 75 hardest Demons on the Demonlist at some point following his completion of Fabrication on September 9, 2020. nSwish also verified Black Lung X, a Main List challenge on the Challenge List. He was the third person to have completed the Top 10 Demons (at the time), after Sunix and Surv and the first person to complete the whole top 75 of the Demonlist (only Zoink could repeat this achievement). His current Top 10 hardest Extreme Demon completions are Sonic Wave Infinity, Tartarus, The Golden, Kenos, Zodiac, Fragile, Hard Machine, Promethean, Thinking Space and Renevant.
